text: Bringing some more Iowa common sense to the swamp! @POTUS met and spoke with Mayor Hart, @SpeakerUpmeyer, & @CRcitymanager about how the Cedar Rapids flood wall funding will fit into his infrastructure plans. #IA01
More good news due to the recently passed tax cuts: Tyson Foods Inc. says more than 100,000 employees will receive bonuses as a result of company savings due to the overhaul of federal tax laws.

Unemployment is the lowest its been in 17 years. The jobs are out there - if one is of working age and physically/mentally able to work they should be working or acquiring job skills necessary to work.
Congress needs to subpoena from the cell service Strzok & Page text messages. Americans deserve to know.

Because of @jeffsessions actions, I’m joining the “Respect State Marijuana Laws” bill. I believe in States' Rights & I’ve seen how cannabis derived medicines can stop seizures in a child, help a veteran cope with pain, or provide relief to a senior with glaucoma. #IA01

To everyone who has written and called into my office with specific parts of the bill that they'd like to see improved, thank you for your input. Your thoughtful contributions helped decide the direction for my efforts to the Conference Committee. #IA01
Tune into @FoxBusiness to join myself and @MelissaAFrancis on @AftertheBell talking tax reform this afternoon.
Looking forward to joining @SimonRadio1776 in a few minutes- tune in for an update from the swamp!

I stand behind my quote in the @washingtonpost: “For us to achieve 3 percent GDP growth over the next 10 years from tax reform, we have to have welfare reform.” Looking forward to working with my colleagues @SenMikeLee & @Jim_Jordan to achieve this.

I have tremendous confidence in @MickMulvaneyOMB to reform the CFPB, excellent choice! CFPB should be subject to Congressional Oversight.

Glad to see that @POTUS @realDonaldTrump budget will reform welfare. Simple: if physically/mentally able to work, you should be working.
